.TH AI-PLAYBOOK-ENV 1 "" "ai-playbook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai\-playbook\-env \- Print a playbook's declared env vars, resolved and redacted
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBai\-playbook\fR env [<slug>] [\-\-file <path>]
.SH DESCRIPTION
env accepts a single playbook source, expressed one of two ways: a bare
positional <slug> (a saved playbook, resolved through the store) or \-\-file
<path> (a raw markdown file, read as\-is). Exactly one source must be given;
zero or more than one is a usage error. It prints the declared env: map as a
\-\-with\-env\-compatible JSON object, resolving each value against the current
process environment (falling back to the declared default) and redacting
sensitive values.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-file\fR \fI<path>\fR
path to a markdown file
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
ai\-playbook env deploy\-staging
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
\fBai\-playbook\fR(1)
